# User roles

A RedSeed <a href="/#users">User</a> can be assigned a single user role. User roles can be used to segment RedSeed reports. User roles are NOT shared between RedSeed client's. User roles are not implemented by all RedSeed clients.

## User role attributes

Attribute | Type | Description
--------- | ------- | -----------
`id` | integer | A unique and autoincrementing identifier for the user which is generated by RedSeed automatically. | true
`description` | text | Role description
`user_count` | integer | The number of users that have this role assigned. Includes archived users.

## Get a single user role

```shell
curl "<%= data.redseed.endpoint %>/user_roles/{ID}" \
  -X GET \
  -H "Authorization: bearer {MY_API_TOKEN}"
```
```php
$curl = curl_init("<%= data.redseed.endpoint %>/user_roles/{ID}");
curl_setopt($curl, CURLOPT_HTTPHEADER, [
  'Authorization: bearer {MY_API_TOKEN}'
]);
$response = curl_exec($curl);
```
```javascript
const redseedApi = require('redseedApi');
let api = redseedApi.authorize('{MY_API_TOKEN}');
let response = api.kittens.get('<%= data.redseed.endpoint %>/user_roles/{ID}');
```

> The above command returns JSON structured like this:

```json
